{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-awesome-timeline-js","path":"/passy/awesome-recursion-schemes/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Track Awesome List"}},"awesomeListMeta":{"readmeParsedAt":"2022-10-13T07:39:58.051Z","repo":"passy/awesome-recursion-schemes","descriptionHTML":"<div>Resources for learning and using recursion schemes.</div>","description":"Resources for learning and using recursion schemes.","stargazerCount":1066,"readmeItemsUpdatedTime":1606309317000,"category":"Theory"},"allAwesomeItem":{"nodes":[{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Articles</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://jtobin.io/promorphisms-pre-post\">Promorphisms, Pre and Post</a> - Practical examples of pre- and postpromorphisms by Jared Tobin.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-11-25T13:01:57.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Articles</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://duplode.github.io/posts/whats-in-a-fold.html\">What's in a Fold: The Basic Catamorphism in recursion-schemes</a> - Introduces catamorphism as a generalization of fold.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-06-15T13:49:29.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Articles</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://free.cofree.io/2017/11/13/recursion/\">Recursion Schemes in Scala</a> - Introduces the fixpoint combinator, anamorphism, catamorphism, hylomorphism, paramorphism, apomorphism, histomorphism, dynamorphism and futumorphism.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-09-21T22:59:19.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Podcasts</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://scala.love/\">Scala Love</a> - Podcast about Scala that brings up\nrecursion schemes in <a href=\"https://scala.love/happy-valentin/\">the second episode</a>.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-05-08T18:47:28.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Podcasts</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.haskellcast.com/\">The Haskell Cast</a> - Recursion schemes come up in\n<a href=\"https://www.haskellcast.com/episode/013-john-wiegley-on-categories-and-compilers\">Episode 13 with John Wiegley</a>.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-05-08T18:47:28.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Introductions</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/passy/awesome-recursion-schemes\">Awesome Recursion Schemes</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/passy/awesome-recursion-schemes\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">1.1k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":1066,\"repo\":\"passy/awesome-recursion-schemes\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - A curation of useful resources for learning about and using recursion schemes.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-01-28T11:14:53.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Implementations</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/slamdata/matryoshka\">Matryoshka</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/slamdata/matryoshka\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">793</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":793,\"repo\":\"slamdata/matryoshka\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> for Scala using Scalaz -\nGeneralized folds, unfolds, and traversals for fixed point data structures.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-01-23T03:20:59.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Implementations</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/andyscott/droste\">andyscott/droste</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/andyscott/droste\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">349</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":349,\"repo\":\"andyscott/droste\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> for Scala using Cats -\nGeneralized folds, unfolds, and traversals for fixed point data structures.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-01-23T03:20:59.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Articles</h2><h3>Hylomorphisms in the Wild</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://bartoszmilewski.com/2017/12/29/stalking-a-hylomorphism-in-the-wild/\">Stalking a Hylomorphism in the Wild</a> - Advent of Code 2017, Domino challenge</li>","updatedAt":"2019-01-13T12:14:07.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Articles</h2><h3>Hylomorphisms in the Wild</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://bartoszmilewski.com/2018/12/20/open-season-on-hylomorphisms/\">Open Seasons on Hylomorphisms</a> - Advent of Code 2018, String comparison challenge</li>","updatedAt":"2019-01-13T12:14:07.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Cheat Sheets</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://ipfs.io/ipfs/QmTppu1VDAQWsdiyVSZX6qb8PErdpwzNP2oKfEhcgaBvWR/guide-to-morphisms.pdf\">The Hitchhiker's Guide to Morphisms</a> - Overview of different morphisms including a printable PDF.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-12-27T10:06:49.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Presentations</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XZ9nPZbaYfE&#x26;t=3s\">Peeling the Banana: Recursion Schemes from First Principles</a> - Zainab Ali's Introductory talk presented at LambdaWorld.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-08-27T14:01:03.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Implementations</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/vmchale/recursion\">recursion</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/vmchale/recursion\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">8</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":8,\"repo\":\"vmchale/recursion\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> for ATS - Demonstration of\nrecursion schemes in ATS.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-07-16T03:08:15.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Implementations</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/sellout/dada\">dada</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/sellout/dada\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">58</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":58,\"repo\":\"sellout/dada\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> for Dhall - a library for recursion\nschemes in Dhall.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-05-07T04:37:48.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Implementations</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/aedans/Katalyst\">Katalyst</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/aedans/Katalyst\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">22</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":22,\"repo\":\"aedans/Katalyst\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> for Kotlin - a re-envisioning based off Matryoshka using lightweight higher kinded polymorphism.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-04-20T03:26:11.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Articles</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://blog.sumtypeofway.com/recursion-schemes-part-v/\">Recursion Schemes, Part V: Hello, Hylomorphisms</a></li>","updatedAt":"2018-04-19T22:54:26.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Articles</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://blog.sumtypeofway.com/recursion-schemes-part-iv-time-is-of-the-essence/\">Recursion Schemes, Part IV: Time is of the Essence</a> - Practical article about histomorphism and the futumorphism.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-03-29T14:49:04.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Implementations</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/vmchale/recursion_schemes/\">recursion_schemes</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/vmchale/recursion_schemes/\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">59</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":59,\"repo\":\"vmchale/recursion_schemes\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> for\nIdris, based off Edward Kmett's Haskell library.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-10-06T19:53:06.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Introductions</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://medium.com/@JosephJnk/recursion-schemes-in-javascript-and-flow-with-static-land-recursision-schemes-97cf10599fb7\">Recursion Schemes in JavaScript and Flow</a> -\nSeries introducing recursion schemes and related concepts in JavaScript,\naimed at developers with a minimal functional programming background.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-09-08T00:58:42.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Implementations</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/JosephJNK/static-land-recursion-schemes\">static-land-recursion-schemes</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/JosephJNK/static-land-recursion-schemes\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">21</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":21,\"repo\":\"JosephJNK/static-land-recursion-schemes\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> for JavaScript/Flow -\nSchemes for data structures written in the style of <a href=\"https://github.com/gcanti/flow-static-land\">flow-static-land</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/gcanti/flow-static-land\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">415</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":415,\"repo\":\"gcanti/flow-static-land\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END-->.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-09-08T00:52:01.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Presentations</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/sellout/recursion-scheme-talk\">recursion-scheme-talk</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/sellout/recursion-scheme-talk\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">204</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":204,\"repo\":\"sellout/recursion-scheme-talk\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Collection of slide decks about recursion schemes.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-08-25T03:32:14.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Implementations</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/slamdata/purescript-matryoshka\">purescript-matryoshka</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/slamdata/purescript-matryoshka\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">57</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":57,\"repo\":\"slamdata/purescript-matryoshka\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> for PureScript -\nWork-in-process port of matryoshka.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-06-06T18:46:57.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Presentations</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-98fR9VmLbQ\">Programming with algebras</a> - Bartosz Milewski's article in talk form, presented at LambdaCon.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-02-07T19:52:20.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Presentations</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=24UoRaoKLjM\">Recursion: Where Functional Programming Hits Bottom</a> - Introduction to recursive fix point data structures and recursion schemes in Haskell and Scala by Greg Pfeil.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-01-21T12:23:10.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Presentations</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5Kr7IykGMzU\">Bracer: Transforming Real-World Languages with Coproducts and Recursion Schemes</a> - High-level talk about structuring programs with coproducts and recursion schemes by Patrick Thomson.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-01-20T09:30:48.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Articles</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://logji.blogspot.co.uk/2012/02/correcting-visitor-pattern.html\">Correcting the Visitor pattern</a> - Showing that the Visitor pattern implements an f-algebra for use with a catamorphism (in Java).</li>","updatedAt":"2017-01-13T11:04:39.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Articles</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://jtobin.io/time-traveling-recursion\">Time Traveling Recursion Schemes</a> - Exploring histo and futu by example by Jared Tobin.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-01-13T10:39:29.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Articles</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/sellout/recursion-scheme-talk/blob/master/cheat%20sheet.pdf\">Cheat Sheet</a> - Map of various recursion schemes and their duals.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-01-12T15:28:41.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Articles</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://jtobin.io/rotating-squares\">Rotating Squares</a> - Using a hylomorphism to rotate a quadtree by Jared Tobin.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-01-10T18:58:01.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Podcasts</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.magicreadalong.com/\">Magic Read Along</a> - Casual discussions about\ncategory theory that often bring up recursion schemes, including <a href=\"http://www.magicreadalong.com/episode/33\">episode\n33</a> which talks about Histomorphisms\nand Futumorphisms.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-01-09T22:10:01.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Articles</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://comonad.com/reader/2009/recursion-schemes/\">Recursion Schemes: A Field Guide (Redux)</a> -\nList of various recursion schemes with code samples.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-01-01T12:23:05.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Papers</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://research.microsoft.com/en-us/um/people/simonpj/Papers/hmap/hmap.ps\">Scrap your boilerplate: a practical design pattern for generic programming, 2003, SPJ et al.</a> -\nDesign pattern for writing programs that traverse data structures built from rich mutually-recursive data types.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-12-30T22:37:25.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Papers</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://maartenfokkinga.github.io/utwente/mmf91m.pdf\">Functional Programming with Bananas, Lenses, Envelopes and Barbed Wire, 1991, Meijer et al.</a> -\nThe original paper most of this is based on.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-12-30T22:35:55.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Introductions</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://jtobin.io/practical-recursion-schemes\">Practical Recursion Schemes</a> -\nIntroduction to pattern functors, fix points, anamorphisms, catamorphisms,\nparamorphisms and hylomorphisms, requiring very little prior knowledge.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-12-30T22:30:02.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Introductions</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://blog.sumtypeofway.com/an-introduction-to-recursion-schemes/\">An Introduction to Recursion Schemes</a> -\nThree-part series in which you discover recursion schemes from scratch and\nimplement a small subset of Edward Kmett's library.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-12-30T22:30:02.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Introductions</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.schoolofhaskell.com/user/bartosz/understanding-algebras\">Understanding Algebras</a> -\nBartosz Milewski explains F-algebras and shows how to use them in the context of\ncatamorphisms.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-12-30T22:30:02.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Articles</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://wiki.haskell.org/Catamorphisms\">Catamorphisms</a> - Definition on the Haskell Wiki.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-12-30T22:30:02.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Articles</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.schoolofhaskell.com/user/edwardk/recursion-schemes/catamorphisms\">Catamorphisms</a> -\nShort definition with code on School of Haskell by Edward Kmett.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-12-30T22:30:02.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Papers</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.cs.ox.ac.uk/ralf.hinze/publications/Sorting.pdf\">A Duality of Sorts, 2013, Hinze et al.</a> -\nShows that many basic sorting algorithms exist as a pair, and that these pairs\narise naturally out of the duality between folds and unfolds.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-12-30T22:30:02.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Papers</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.cs.ox.ac.uk/people/daniel.james/sorting/sorting.pdf\">Sorting with Bialgebras and Distributive Laws, 2012, Hinze et al.</a> -\nShows how paramorphisms and apomorphisms can be used for more efficient\nimplementations of sorting algorithms.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-12-30T22:30:02.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Presentations</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.timphilipwilliams.com/slides.html\">Slidedecks by Tim Philip Williams</a> -\n\"Recursion Schemes by Example\" and \"Exotic Tools for Exotic Trades\" provide\nconcise definitions as well as practical examples of many recursion schemes.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-12-30T22:30:02.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Presentations</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9EGYSb9vov8\">Unifying Structured Recursion Schemes</a> -\n12 min presentation by Ralf Hinze, Nicolas Wu, and Jeremy Gibbons.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-12-30T22:30:02.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Presentations</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Zw9KeP3OzpU\">Recursion Schemes</a> -\nPresented by Tim Williams at the London Haskell meetup.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-12-30T22:30:02.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Presentations</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=PK4SOaAGVfg\">F-algebras or: How I Learned to Stop Worrying and Love the Type System</a> -\nPresented by Anthony Burzillo at the NYC Haskell User's Group.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-12-30T22:30:02.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Presentations</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=i5A2Amfcir8\">A Gentle Introduction to Recursion Schemes</a> -\nPresented by Jean Remi Desjardins at Lambdaconf 2016.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-12-30T22:30:02.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Implementations</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/ekmett/recursion-schemes/\">recursion-schemes</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/ekmett/recursion-schemes/\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">310</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":310,\"repo\":\"ekmett/recursion-schemes\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> for\nHaskell - The canonical implementation by Edward Kmett.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-12-30T22:30:02.000Z"}]},"previous":{"id":"awesomes/github.com/rossant/awesome-math","repo":"rossant/awesome-math"},"next":{"id":"awesomes/github.com/erwanlemerrer/awesome-audit-algorithms","repo":"erwanlemerrer/awesome-audit-algorithms"}},"pageContext":{"repo":"passy/awesome-recursion-schemes","id":"awesomes/github.com/passy/awesome-recursion-schemes","previousId":"awesomes/github.com/rossant/awesome-math","nextId":"awesomes/github.com/erwanlemerrer/awesome-audit-algorithms"}},"staticQueryHashes":["228695001","2744905544","2828988102"]}